Well,

	Just so we don't become TOO anti-establishmental here.. lets just
remember that it was big business, and corporate attitude that provided,
designed, created, and ultimately built these Volkswagens that we drive
around in. Dunno about you guys, bust most of the Volkswagen busses that the
hippies drove around back in the day were purchased by their conservative
parents. (just as parents buy their kids Honda Civics now, and how parents
bought their kids TransAms in the late 70s).  Personally, I bought my own
first car (a crappy 4 cyl 1984 Toyota Corolla for a grand). But lets not
forget too, that it's ultimately the big businesses that provide the
redesign, sales, and manufacturing of the parts we use.  

Sure, the big guys get big tax breaks, but.. they also pay the most taxes,
and if we keep bashing them, sooner or later they're not going to foot the
bill anymore. And unless we all become proficient welders, metalurgists, and
metal fabricators.. we're going to be S**T out of luck for parts. Just
remember... the parts people, Volkswagen of America, etc.. are not owned by
hippies. They're owned by business oriented investors.

Personally, I have nothing against hippies... I think they make great music,
and provide for an interesting clothing line.


